On the voyage, the streame and towns of the Tarentino gulf, of Sicily, of the Campanian coast, are named as the ijan exiles pass. Hardly a place in Latium is unnoticed, when they are lauded: and the embassies, the friendly visits, the catalogues uf confederata Latins (vii. 641), and of allied Tuscans (a 143), are used for the same purpose. Etruria, Umbria, Campania, Picenum, Samnium, the Aequi, Volsci, Hernici, Marsi, Aurunci-all the famous tribe-names and the oldest settlements are introduced with skill and picturesque variety.
